    <text id="A9510T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Junkin writes to McFarland asking his assistance for the upcoming Communion
                    service at his church.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-06-02">June 2<hi rend="super"><hi rend="underline">d</hi></hi> 1862</date>
                        <name type="place">New Providence Manse</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear D<hi rend="super">
                            <hi rend="underline">r</hi>
                        </hi> M<hi rend="super">
                            <hi rend="underline">c</hi>
                        </hi>Farland</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>We have determined to have our summer communion on next <abbr expan="Sabbath"
                        >Sab.</abbr> week (3<hi rend="super">
                        <hi rend="underline">d</hi>
                    </hi> Sab. of June). I expect to have <abbr expan="Brother">Bro.</abbr> Walker
                    with me during the meeting, which will commence on Friday; but the Session
                    expressed a desire that I should write &amp; ask you also to be with us.
                    Some of your old friends wish very much to see &amp; hear you again. Mr
                    Morrison I know would be greatly gratified to meet you. He was out yesterday,
                    but I did not get to speak to him. <pb n="2"/>I believe he is in his usual
                    health.</p>

                <p><abbr expan="Brother">Bro.</abbr> Harris would supply your pulpit for you I have
                    no doubt.</p>

                <p>Remember me kindly to Mrs. M<hi rend="super">c</hi>Farland &amp; your family.
                    If you come bring her with you &amp; make us a little visit. Hoping that you
                    will be able to comply with our request.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>I remain yours truly in Christ</salute>
                    <signed>E.D. Junkin</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
